  m_text: "The graceful decorator crab is a slender crab known for its long legs
    and remarkable camouflage\r\nbehavior. Like other decorator crabs, it attaches
    pieces of algae, sponges, and other small\r\norganisms to hooked hairs on its
    shell, creating a living disguise that helps it blend into the\r\nseafloor. In
    the ocean, fashion and survival go claw in claw!\r"
