  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: Colonial tube worms grow in dense clusters around hydrothermal vents on
    the deep seafloor. Each worm lives inside a protective white tube and extends
    a bright red plume used to absorb chemicals and oxygen from the surrounding water.
    Instead of eating, they rely on symbiotic bacteria inside their bodies to convert
    vent chemicals into energy. All dressed up in tubes with nowhere to go!
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
