  m_text: "The basking shark is the second-largest fish in the world, growing up
    to ten meters long. Instead of hunting large prey, it swims with it's mouth open
    to filter microscopic plankton from the water using specialized gills. Despite
    it's intimidating size, it is a slow-moving and harmless giant. The basking shark
    believes in one rule: keep calm and filter on!\r"
