  m_text: "The giant sunflower star is one of the largest and fastest sea stars,
    growing up to one meterwide with as many as twenty-four arms. It crawls across
    the seafloor using thousands of tubefeet while hunting clams, snails, and sea
    urchins. By controlling sea urchin populations, it plays an important role in
    protecting kelp forest ecosystems. It\u2019s truly the star of the sea!"
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
